  "title": "Tapping for stillness without dread",
  "subtitle": "A five-minute tapping script for releasing the association between quiet and the sense that something bad is about to happen.",
  "excerpt": "A five-minute tapping practice from Day 19 of the SLEEP program. The script targets the pattern of waiting for the other shoe to drop during periods of calm, the nervous system that has learned to read peace as a warning sign.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Adapted from Day 19 of SLEEP: A 30-Day Tapping Intensive (Rebecca J Page, 2025), \"Stillness without dread.\" Tapping framework: Gary Craig's Emotional Freedom Technique (EFT), in use since the mid-1990s, building on Roger Callahan's Thought Field Therapy.",
